        <p>Converts the cursor to Bubble mode, which lets you create a callout by clicking in the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic,Products.MovieSync">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> and dragging a rectangle area. When you release the cursor, a "bubble" shape is created, which consists of a rectangular or square area for holding text and a pointy area for pointing toward an area of the image that you want to explain or emphasize. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic,Products.Capture">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../UI_Elements/Bubble_Properties_Dialog.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Bubble Properties Dialog</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
